+.codex/I-gen-002-phase3\codex_diff_audit_iter_2.txt:3254:.codex\I-bench-001\codex_diff_audit.txt:1663:Per-claim citation precision (does the cited source actually support the claim it's attached to?) is qualitative and **cannot be deterministically scored without ground-truth claim-source mappings**. Plan v13 §F names "citation precision/recall ≥ baseline" but for benchmark purposes precision is approximated via a Phase-3 spot-check protocol: human reviewer audits 10 random claim-citation pairs per template, scores `# verified` / 10. The aggregate precision-spot-check is the user-side verification at Phase 3 close. NO LLM-as-judge — would re-introduce the very subjectivity the rubric exists to eliminate.
+.codex/I-gen-002-phase3\codex_diff_audit_iter_2.txt:3255:.codex\I-bench-001\codex_diff_audit.txt:1665:**Phase 0 D2 score = D2a only** (quantity). Phase 3 D2 score combines D2a + D2b at equal weight; D2c spot-check is recorded as a separate qualitative gate at Phase 3 close.
